# Coding standards

- Use consistent naming: PascalCase for classes and public members, camelCase for local variables and parameters.
- Keep methods under 30 lines. Extract helper methods for complex logic.
- Every public API must have XML doc comments (C#) or JSDoc (TypeScript).
- No magic numbers — use named constants.
- Prefer early returns over deeply nested conditionals.
- All async methods must propagate cancellation tokens where available.
- Do not commit commented-out code. Remove dead code before merging.
